“Your actions will determine our fate,” was, without doubt, the main message issued by President Cyril Ramaphosa as he announced the reopening of the economy as the country moves to lockdown Level 3 from 1 June. On Sunday evening, day 59 since the lockdown was first implemented in late March, Ramaphosa announced the relaxation of a number of restrictions, including the removal of a curfew on the movement of people, the removal of limitations on outdoor exercise, the return to work of most business sectors, the sale of liquor for home consumption only – on specified days and for limited...